Work with remote Frappe sites without direct bench access.

This enables the "remote-site" development flow - the third major weg workflow
alongside app-centric and bench-centric development.

Commands:
  clone    Clone a remote site's customizations to a local git-backed directory
  pull     Fetch changes from the remote site
  push     Push local changes to the remote site
  sync     Bidirectional sync with optional commit message
  status   Show differences between local and remote

The remote workflow creates a git-backed directory that mirrors the site's
customization structure, enabling:
  - Local file editing with AI assistance
  - Version control via git
  - Team collaboration through git workflows
  - Easy migration to proper Frappe apps

Example workflow:
  weg remote clone https://mysite.frappe.cloud mysite
  cd mysite
  # Edit files locally...
  weg remote sync -m "Add priority field to Todo"

Usage:
  weg remote [command]

Available Commands:
  clone       Clone a remote site's customizations
  info        Show information about the remote site
  login       Save credentials for a remote site
  logout      Remove saved credentials for a remote site
  pull        Pull changes from the remote site
  push        Push local changes to the remote site
  status      Show sync status between local and remote
  sync        Bidirectional sync with the remote site

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for remote

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts

Use "weg remote [command] --help" for more information about a command.
